subNode:value.scalar:string: Display sales evolution and orders by status.
" method="post" style="float: right; margin-left: 10px;"> <select name="id_country"> <option value="0"

The following graphs represent the evolution of your e-store's orders and sales turnover for a selected period. This tool is one that you should use often as it allows you to quickly monitor your store's viability. This feature also allows you to monitor multiple time periods, and only valid orders are graphically represented.
You can view order distribution below.

In your Back Office, you can modify the following order statuses: Awaiting Check Payment, Payment Accepted, Preparation in Progress, Shipping, Delivered, Cancelled, Refund, Payment Error, Out of Stock, and Awaiting Bank Wire Payment.
These order statuses cannot be removed from the Back Office, however you have the option to add more.

SELECT o.`invoice_date`, o.`total_paid_real` / o.conversion_rate AS total_paid_real, SUM(od.product_quantity) as product_quantity FROM `
SELECT osl.`name`, COUNT(oh.`id_order`) as total FROM `
order_state_lang` osl ON (os.`id_order_state` = osl.`id_order_state` AND osl.`id_lang` =
order_history` oh ON os.`id_order_state` = oh.`id_order_state` LEFT JOIN `
order_history` ios WHERE ios.`id_order` = oh.`id_order` ORDER BY ios.`date_add` DESC, oh.`id_order_history` DESC LIMIT 1 )
